PN,36905
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F369A1781294762
OL,3,CChild killer stabbed 25 times in his
OL,4,Ccell
OL,6,FTaylor who boasted about his ability
OL,7,Fto make makeshift weapons, and had
OL,8,Frecently been transferred to Wakefield
OL,9,Fin relation to the murder of an
OL,10,Fassociate, to which he pleaded guilty,
OL,11,Fand the attempted murder of a police
OL,12,Fofficer, for which he was convicted.
OL,14,FMr Pitter also shared HMP Wakefield's
OL,15,Funique prisoner arrangement in that
OL,16,Fthe HMP wing had an "open door"
OL,17,Fpolicy, allowing Main Prisoners (MPs)
OL,18,Fand Vulnerable prisoners (VPs) to
OL,19,Ffreely interact during association.
OL,26,@xD@UOUxD@_O]
OL,1,Woz5~k4{$z%~s1z5jw=hw1         G5/7
OL,2,W,.!+.!/*%/*%,.!/*%/*%/"-$T,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BYorks News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,370,360,260,120,000,100
PN,36906
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F369A1781294762
OL,3,CChild killer stabbed 25 times in his
OL,4,Ccell
OL,6,FThis mixing contributed to significant
OL,7,Ftension, as MPs indicated they did not
OL,8,Fwant to be housed with sex offenders
OL,9,For those who committed offences
OL,10,Fagainst children. The prosecutor said
OL,11,FVPs were bullied, creating "an element
OL,12,Fof fear amongst some VPs".
OL,14,FHe told the jury: "You may feel that
OL,15,Fthe system in operation meant that the
OL,16,Fprison guards were not able to keep an
OL,17,Feye on all prisoners at all times."
OL,18,FBevan "kept himself to himself" and
OL,19,Fwould mainly stay in his cell, often
OL,20,Fasking to be locked inside.
OL,26,@sD@\OUtD@YO]vD@SOUyD@cO]zD@GOUzD@_O]
OL,1,Woz5~k4{$z%~s1z5jw=hw1         G6/7
